Explanation:

1. Create a graph to represent the dislikes between people.
2. Iterate through the graph to mark odd vertices (those who have an odd degree).
3. If any odd vertex is found, return false, as it means there is no bipartite graph.
4. If all vertices are even, return true, indicating that a bipartite graph exists.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) and space complexity of O(n), where n is the number of people. The energy implications are low as it only requires a small amount of energy to solve the problem.

